Top picks: “Lesser Known Monsters” and “Faith, Hope, and Carnage.” I cannot recommend either of them enough.

Absolutely humbled to announce our first project, AFTERCARE, will be have its World Premiere at @tiff_net 2023 as part of the always excellent and equally eclectic Short Cuts Programme. Press release at link in bio. Tickets on sale August 28th.

Couldn’t be more thankful for all the souls below.

My favourite part about this @playbackinstagram article is not that I’m in the first sentence (but also, ayooo); it’s that they used @kaniehtiio as a segue to introduce our film 😭 What a fam jam.

Opening weekend, baby ✍🏽

World Premiere, Saturday, September 9, 1845. Public sale on August 28th. We don’t get to reserve any tickets so, like, I don’t know, use your Beyoncé/Taylor Swift refresh skills on this one.

GUESS WHOSE SHORT FILM IS PREMIERING AT TIFF?! 🤗🎬🥳 And opening weekend, no less! 😏

So unbelievably proud of my girl @anubhamomin who’s making a splash with her directorial debut! AFTERCARE will be part of @tiff_net’s 2023 Short Cuts Programme and you’re not gonna wanna miss it. Tickets go on sale August 28th!

Humbled to have been a part of @abovethepalace’s first project as 2nd AD and oh so grateful that Anubha brought me on despite my lack of industry experience and gave me the opportunity to learn from and work with the brilliant @pjmarcellino. 

Yay to friends who bring us along for the ride as the rise 💫👯‍♀️

🎬🎞️🍿🎥

Had our first press event for AFTERCARE last week at @tiff_net’s celebration of Canadian filmmakers at this year’s festival. Thank you @tenderwench, @maikaharper (our stars), @justineabigail (our 2nd AD), and @rodneydiverlus (my emotional support producer) for absolutely dominating the day while I foraged for mushrooms on the side of a mountain in southern France.

Red carpet photos by the always wonderful @georgepimentel1.

#tiff23

We’re @playbackinstagram official!

Big takeaways: our origin, our ethos, and our exciting collaboration with @oncanadaproject. More to come, very soon 😘

Okay, but why does this one go so hard?

“With Above the Palace’s dedication to diversity, impactful storytelling, and fresh narratives, it’s poised to revolutionize the entertainment landscape, providing much-needed representation and engaging content for audiences worldwide."

Shoutout to @caribbeancameranow for the love. For the community, by the community!

August 📚 Top reads: Hello Beautiful, Free, and The Rachel Incident

Look, it’s like we have our own set of trading cards 🥹

Very into asking not only (or at all) “what have you done?” but also (or instead) “what do you want to do?” to anyone at any stage of life. Thank you @lauradecarufel, @sarahjlaing, @thekitca, @thetorontostar, and @tiff_net for seeing power in the new.

Forever loving on @aarluk and @alethea_aggiuq and @qanurli for the forever perspective change.

Et grâce à @royalgilbert for framing my “power” as soft femme joy 🖤

A special slide for special people. It’s my favourite one. 

Extra big squeeze for @vikileaks_, who was our last minute, unexpected afterparty producer, and to @samkrish_ for the balloon that welcomed our day of celebration.

Thanks @dgctalent 🥹

Congratulations to the nominees and our entire AFTERCARE team🩸
September 2023 📚 Top top top pick: Tom Lake

If you saw us at @tiff_net and thought, “Oh hey, they cute,” please know that the biggest thanks go to 1) Our mamas for the face cards, and 2) the incomparable Kelly Henderson of @house.of.hendo for the LEWKS. Kelly’s work is upcycled from thrifted, deadstock, or vintage fabrics — everything from tablecloth to couch upholstery (!) — and is bespoke, genderless, made beautifully in Toronto, and full of as much whimsy as the artist herself.

Kelly, we are so, so honoured to have you as a collaborator and friend 💜 Thank you for making our TIFF début so very gorgeous.

In September, House of Hendo had the extreme pleasure of dressing the pure talent that is the @abovethepalace team @sandymhudson @anubhamomin @rodneydiverlus while showcasing and promoting their short film AFTERCARE at @tiff_net 

Damn fine beings, inwards and out.
All I’m saying is get ready to go above and beyond the palace people!!

I’m still processing all the excellence that has happened for HOH over the last month, but humbly grateful people have gravitated to the clothing and it’s colourful energy.

Elated to announce our second festival screening will be on beautiful Prince Edward Island at the @charlottetownfilmfest 🍂 

AFTERCARE will screen at 6:30PM on lucky Friday, October 13th as part of Shorts Programme 1. Full schedule and tickets/passes available on the #chff website. And beyond the festival, we have some wonderful community-based programming in the works — stay tuned for more as we gear up to touch on down the island’s famous red shores 👒

October 2023 📕 Top reads: Lenni and Margot; Black Butterflies; All the Little Bird-Hearts

Announcement time. AFTERCARE will play at @regentparkfilm as part of their Face to Face Shorts program on November 25th from 6-7:30pm. Proud to be part of a festival that is strong, vocal, and intentional in its solidarity and ethos.

November 2023, and it’s hard to pick the top reads as I super recommend them all. But, for sure, Herzog’s memoir, “Birnam Wood,” and “The Glutton” are books I will think about, often, for a very long time.
December 2023 📚 Top read: How to Say Babylon, for sure.
